---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="about"
	description="The person behind Crossing Dreams and the scholarship that (hopefully) changes everything."
	pubDate={new Date('March 18 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		Hi, I'm the person behind <em>Crossing Dreams</em>. This blog was born from a very specific dream:
		getting the GKS scholarship and living in South Korea. And from the need to document everything
		that happens along the way — the process, the waiting, learning Korean from scratch, and someday
		(fingers crossed) real life there.
	</p>

	<p>
		I'm from Latin America, passionate about languages, food, travel, and the small things that make
		everyday life feel full. It took me a while to dare to apply for something this big. But here I am.
	</p>

	<h2>What this blog is about</h2>

	<p>
		<strong>The GKS process.</strong> Everything I learn about the scholarship, the application,
		the documents, and the waiting. Because when I searched for information, I couldn't find enough.
	</p>

	<p>
		<strong>Learning Korean.</strong> Resources, methods, mistakes, and progress. No filters.
	</p>

	<p>
		<strong>Korean life and culture.</strong> Dramas, music, food, aesthetics — the things that made
		me fall in love with this country before ever setting foot there.
	</p>

	<p>
		<strong>And when the time comes:</strong> real life in Korea. Adjusting, university, friendships,
		traveling within the country. All of it.
	</p>

	<h2>Why "Crossing Dreams"?</h2>

	<p>
		Because crossing a dream — the ocean, the language, the scholarship, the fear — is exactly what
		I'm trying to do. And because writing about it helps me remember why I started.
	</p>
</Layout>
